14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 28 O.S. 2021, Section 121, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 121. A. In all cases where publication of legal
18 notices is required or allowed by law, the person or official
19 desiring publication shall be required to pay:
20 1. For all matters other than tabular matter, fourteen cents
21 ($0.14) per word for first insertion, and thirteen cents ($0.13) per
22 word for each subsequent insertion, with each separate group of
23 numerals included in the matter to be counted as one word,
24 regardless of the number of digits involved;
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2167 Page 1
1 2. Effective November 1, 2005, for all matters other than
2 tabular matter, fifteen cents ($0.15) twenty-two cents ($0.22) per
3 word for first insertion, and fourteen cents ($0.14) twenty cents
4 ($0.20) per word for each subsequent insertion, with each separate
5 group of letters or numerals included in the matter to be counted as
6 one word, regardless of the number of digits involved. Elimination
7 of space between words or numeric descriptions, or the use of
8 hyphenation to combine words or numeric descriptions is prohibited;
9 and
10 3. 2. For all tabular matter, in not to exceed eight-point
11 type, including, but not limited to, graphics, maps, seals,
12 signature blocks, forms, spreadsheets, lists of persons, firms, and
13 corporations whose personal property taxes are delinquent and lists
14 of lands and town lots upon which taxes are delinquent, seventy
15 cents ($0.70) One Dollar and ten cents ($1.10) per line per
16 newspaper column in width, for first insertion, and sixty-five cents
17 ($0.65) One Dollar ($1.00) per line per newspaper column in width,
18 for each subsequent insertion. A standard tabular line shall be a
19 minimum of one and one-half (1.5) inches in width;
20 3. A newspaper qualified to publish notices under the laws of
21 this state has the authority to publish all notices in a format
22 readable to a reasonable person. Type size used for notices shall
23 be no less than eight-point noncondensed type, with a maximum of
24 ten-point noncondensed type, unless a larger type size is requested
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2167 Page 2
1 in w riting by the person desiring the notice. Any notice submitted
2 to a newspaper which is unreadable or intended to be unreadable may
3 be rejected or typeset by the newspaper in a readable format;
4 4. Newspapers providing affidavits or proof of publication are
5 permitted to charge and collect a fee for a notarial act as defined
6 in Section 5 of Title 49 of the Oklahoma Statutes or Section 209 of
7 Title 49 of the Oklahoma Statutes as applicable;
8 5. For any notice placed in a newspaper, there shall be a
9 minimum charge of Twenty-five Dollars ($25.00) for such notice if
10 the total calculated cost of words and lines described in paragraphs
11 1 and 2 of this subsection is less than Twenty-five Dollars
12 ($25.00);
13 6. When notice by publication in a newspaper is required by
14 law, order of court, or other means, the newspaper publishing the
15 notice shall, at no additional cost to the person or official
16 desiring the notice, cause the notice to be placed on the newspaper
17 website if the newspaper operates a website, in front of any paywall
18 or paid access to the website. Additionally, the newspaper shall
19 upload notices to a statewide website established and maintained as
20 a joint venture of a majority of Oklahoma newspapers qualified to
21 publish notices by the laws of this state. Posting of notices on
22 the newspaper website and statewide website shall be performed in a
23 timely manner but shall not invalidate the publication of a notice
24 otherwise valid when published in the newspaper. Temporary outages
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2167 Page 3
1 or s ervice interruptions prohibiting the posting or display of such
2 notice shall be considered harmless error and the proper legal
3 notice requirements shall be considered met if the notice published
4 in the newspaper otherwise complies with the requirements for
5 publication. Access to the statewide website shall be free to the
6 public; and
7 7. Any person or official required to publish a notice shall
8 submit the notice in writing or by electronic means by the deadline
9 established by the newspaper for such notices. No deadline shall be
10 set by the newspaper that is more than five (5) business days prior
11 to the date of publication, excluding the date of publication,
12 Saturdays, Sundays, and legal holidays in the State of Oklahoma.
13 Upon request, the newspaper shall confirm receipt of the notice and
14 notify the person or official in writing or by electronic means of
15 the dates of the issue or issues in which the notice shall appear.
16 If the newspaper fails to publish the notice in the issue
17 specified in the confirmation, the newspaper shall publish the
18 notice in a future issue specified by the person or official
19 desiring the notice at no charge. If the notice has multiple
20 insertions, only the first notice omitted by the newspaper shall be
21 required to run at no charge.
22 B. The county treasurer shall collect the cost of publication
23 of lists of lands and town lots sold for delinquent taxes at
24 original sale or resale from the individuals purchasing the lands
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2167 Page 4
1 and town lots at the sale or resale involved, and shall deposit all
2 monies collected to the credit of the fund of the county which paid
3 the cost of publication. The publisher of the notice shall be paid
4 for the publication of the notice from the general fund of the
5 county or, if monies are not available in the general fund of the
6 county at the time of publication, from the "Resale-Property Fund"
7 of the county.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
9 Passed the House of Representatives the 25th day of March, 2025.
